

## Make a SQL table

~~~sh
mydb=SOMEDATABASEFILE.sqlite
# the command
sqlite3 $mydb \
<<< "
.headers on
SELECT *
FROM inspections
LIMIT 5;
" |
sed 's/^/|/' | sed 's/$/|/' |
sed -e '1a\
|-' | sed -e '$a\
{:.table-sql}'
~~~

Alternatively:

~~~sh
function qtq(){
  sed -e '1i\
  .headers on
' | sqlite3 $mydb |
sed 's/^/|/' | sed 's/$/|/' |
sed -e '1a\
|-' | sed -e '$a\
{:.table-sql}'
}
~~~


Usage:

~~~sh
$ qtq <<< "SELECT * FROM sometable;"
~~~

Or better yet:

~~~sh
$ pbpaste | qtq | pbcopy
~~~


Or even better:

~~~sh
$ pbpaste | qtq | tee /dev/tty | pbcopy
~~~


